// OOP theory 

1. Class defination:
Class is a blueprint for creating objects. It defines the properties and behavior of the object. 

2. Object defination: 
Object is an instance of a class. It has its own state and behavior.

a) Encapsulations: 
The process of combining data and functions into a single unit is called encapsulation.

b) Inheritance:
The process of creating a new class from an existing class is called inheritance.

c) Abstraction: 
The process of hiding the internal details and showing only the essential features is called abstraction.

d) Polymorphism: 
The process of having many forms is called polymorphism.

